# Create Base Infrastructure for `base_infra` Repository

Implement the **infra-platform** layer from [Infrastructure Design_solo.md](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/Infrastructure%20Design_solo.md) — the shared infrastructure that creates Docker networks, runs data stores (PostgreSQL, Redis), reverse proxy (NGINX), and observability stack (Prometheus, Grafana, Loki, **Promtail**, Jaeger). Application repos (`chat-api`, `rag-service`) are **out of scope** — they will join these networks as `external: true` later.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope**: This plan creates only the **infra-platform** layer. The `chat-api` and `rag-service` repos are separate and not included.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **SSL/TLS**: NGINX will be configured for HTTP only initially. SSL termination (Let's Encrypt / certbot) can be added when deploying to a real server. The config includes a placeholder `server` block ready for HTTPS upgrade.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Promtail added**: The original design doc suggested using the Loki Docker log driver (no Promtail container). Per your request, we're adding **Promtail** as a dedicated log collector instead. Promtail mounts the Docker socket to auto-discover containers and ships logs to Loki with labels (container name, compose service, etc.).

---

