---

### Core Compose & Environment

#### [NEW] [docker-compose.yml](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/docker-compose.yml)

- Creates 2 Docker networks: `frontend-net`, `internal-net`
- 8 services: **nginx**, **postgres** (16 + pgvector), **redis** (7), **prometheus**, **grafana**, **loki**, **promtail**, **jaeger**
- Resource limits per design (tuned for 4 vCPU / 8 GB)
- Health checks for postgres, redis, nginx
- Named volumes for persistent data (`pg_data`, `redis_data`, `prometheus_data`, `grafana_data`, `loki_data`, `promtail_positions`)
- Startup dependency order: postgres + redis → nginx; loki → grafana
- NGINX starts and returns 502/503 until app backends are up (by design)

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/.env.example)

- All required environment variables with placeholder values
- `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `CHAT_DB_PASSWORD`, `RAG_DB_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`
- `GF_SECURITY_ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `GF_SERVER_ROOT_URL`

#### [NEW] [.gitignore](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/.gitignore)

- Ignore `.env`, backup files, volumes, OS files

---

### NGINX (Reverse Proxy)

#### [NEW] [nginx.conf](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/nginx/nginx.conf)

- Main nginx config with worker processes, logging, gzip
- Includes `conf.d/*.conf`

#### [NEW] [upstreams.conf](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/nginx/conf.d/upstreams.conf)

- Upstream blocks for `chat-api:8000` and `rag-api:8001`

#### [NEW] [routes.conf](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/nginx/conf.d/routes.conf)

- HTTP server block on port 80
- Route `/api/chat/` → chat-api upstream
- Route `/api/rag/` → rag-api upstream
- Health endpoint at `/nginx-health`
- `proxy_next_upstream` for graceful handling when app backends aren't up yet

---

### PostgreSQL

#### [NEW] [init.sql](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/postgres/init.sql)

- Creates `chat_app` and `rag_app` roles with password variables
- Grants `CREATEDB` privilege so apps can manage their own schemas/migrations
- Installs `pgvector` extension
- **No schemas created** — each application manages its own schema lifecycle

#### [NEW] [pg_hba.conf](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/postgres/pg_hba.conf)

- `scram-sha-256` auth for all network connections
- Trust for local Unix socket (used by health checks)

---

### Observability — Prometheus

#### [NEW] [prometheus.yml](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/prometheus/prometheus.yml)

- Global scrape interval: 15s
- Scrape targets: `chat-api:8000/metrics`, `rag-api:8001/metrics`
- Self-monitoring: `prometheus:9090/metrics`

---

### Observability — Loki

#### [NEW] [loki-config.yml](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/loki/loki-config.yml)

- Single-process mode (appropriate for solo)
- BoltDB Shipper for index, filesystem for chunks
- Retention: 7 days
- Listen on `:3100`

---

### Observability — Grafana

#### [NEW] [datasources.yml](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/grafana/provisioning/datasources/datasources.yml)

- Prometheus datasource → `http://prometheus:9090`
- Loki datasource → `http://loki:3100`

> [!NOTE]
> **Dashboards and alerting** are deferred — add them when you have real traffic patterns to monitor.

---

### Observability — Promtail

#### [NEW] [promtail-config.yml](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/promtail/promtail-config.yml)

- Server on `:9080` (HTTP) and `:0` (gRPC disabled)
- Positions file for tracking read offsets
- `docker_sd_configs` to auto-discover containers via Docker socket
- Relabeling: extracts `container_name`, `compose_service`, `compose_project` as Loki labels
- Pushes logs to `http://loki:3100/loki/api/v1/push`

---

### Scripts

#### [NEW] [backup.sh](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/scripts/backup.sh)

- `pg_dumpall` via docker compose exec
- Gzip compression, 7-day retention
- Exactly as specified in design doc

#### [NEW] [healthcheck.sh](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/scripts/healthcheck.sh)

- Checks all infra services are running and healthy
- Checks postgres and redis connectivity
- Checks NGINX, Grafana, Prometheus, Jaeger HTTP endpoints

---

### Project Files

#### [NEW] [Makefile](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/Makefile)

- `up`, `down`, `logs`, `status`, `backup`, `db-shell`, `health`
- No `deploy-all` at this stage

#### [NEW] [README.md](file:///Users/surachai/dev/base_infra/README.md)

- Quick start guide
- Prerequisites (Docker, Docker Compose)
- Network architecture overview
- Promtail log collection architecture explanation
- Port map table
- Daily ops checklist reference
